saadadb.query.matchpattern
Class QEToolBox

java.lang.Object
  saadadb.query.matchpattern.QEToolBox

public abstract class QEToolBox
extends java.lang.Object

Povide some usefull tools for the Query Engine of Saada

WARNING: for all operations involving Index and BitSet, List (of Long,Double) and/or BitSet must have the same order! (Double 1 of a list = Long(OID) 1 of an other list = bit 1 of a BitSet). See the method used to load Indexes to assure this is the case! Saada Web Site.

Version:
1.33, 25/10/2006
Author:
Pineau Francois-Xavier
See Also:
nothing

fusionIndexBitSet

public static KeyIndex fusionIndexBitSet(KeyIndex ref_index,
                                         KeyIndex append_index)
Returns a BitSet Index (structure like Map<Long,BitSet>) resulting from the fusion of two other BitSet Index.

Exemple:
    bs1: L1->{1,1,0,1} ; L2->{0,0,0,1}
    bs2: L1->{0,1,1,1} ; L2->{1,0,1,0}
    returns: L1->{0,1,0,1} ; L2->{0,0,0,0}

WARNING:
   1) The two specified BitSte Indexes are modified by the method (one is returned, the other is clear)!
   2) Two BitSte associed with the same Key must have the same size!

Returns:
A BitSet Index (same structure as bs1) where for each Key the BitSet is the result of a logical "AND" between BitSet associed with that Key in specified BitSet Indexes

unionWithDifferentKey

public static KeyIndex unionWithDifferentKey(KeyIndex ref_index,
                                             LongCPIndex append_index)
Returns a Map containing for each Key of the two specified Map a Collection view of all Object present in Collection values associated with the same Key. If a Key of one of the Map is not present in the second one, the corresponding Entry of the returned Map is the same as the one of the Map containing the Key.

WARNING: the two specified Map are modified by the method (one is returned, the other is clear)!

Parameters:
paramA - a Map which structure is like Map<Object,Collection<Object>>
paramB - a Map which structure is the same as paramA (same type of Object)
Returns:
A Map where each Key is associed with a Collection containing all Objects present in value(s) associed with that Key in M1 and/or M2

fusionOID

public static KeyIndex fusionOID(KeyIndex paramA,
                                 KeyIndex paramB)
Returns a Set containing elements present in both the two specified Set. We use here the method retainAll.

NOTE:
     1) If specified Set paramA is a LinkedHashSet its order is conserved.
     2) If you have two LinkedHashSet, put the smaller as paramA (if you don't care the order of paramB).

WARNING: the two specified Set are modified by the method (one is returned with modifications, the other is clear)!

Parameters:
paramA - a Set
paramB - a Set which Objects are the same as paramA ones
Returns:
A Map where each Key is associed with a Collection containing all Objects present in value(s) associed with that Key in M1 and/or M2
